{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596055","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596055"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:09:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15388"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15388","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15388"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.29,0,0.04,0.29,0.39]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8079"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63604"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8079","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8079"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15388"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49051"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"504"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4967"},{"type":"tags","id":"4978"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"11618"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19608"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19611"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20857"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45795"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63604"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents with a six-month history of recurrent abdominal pain and altered bowel habits. She has been diagnosed with irritable bowel syndrome after appropriate investigations excluded organic disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVarious strategies can be considered in the treatment of this condition. These include dietary and lifestyle advice on regular exercise and improved quality of sleep. Cognitive behavioural therapy does have a place and some medications such as antidepressants can help.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is also a role for complementary therapies and the patient would like to know which one might benefit her.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following interventions has the strongest evidence for its efficacy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acupuncture","Aloe vera","Evening primrose oil","Peppermint oil","St John\u0027s wort"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMultiple systematic reviews and meta-analyses have shown that \u003Cstrong\u003Epeppermint oil\u003C/strong\u003E is effective for treating irritable bowel syndrome symptoms, particularly abdominal pain and global symptoms. The mechanism involves smooth muscle relaxation through calcium channel blockade.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eacupuncture\u003C/strong\u003E has been studied, evidence for its efficacy is limited and inconsistent. \u003Cstrong\u003EEvening primrose oil\u003C/strong\u003E has not shown significant benefit in clinical trials for irritable bowel syndrome. \u003Cstrong\u003EAloe vera\u003C/strong\u003E has limited evidence supporting its use, with some studies showing no benefit over placebo. \u003Cstrong\u003ESt John\u0027s wort\u003C/strong\u003E has not been well-studied for irritable bowel syndrome specifically.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Irritable bowel syndrome can be managed with multiple evidence-based treatments including dietary modifications, psychological interventions, and certain complementary therapies.","Peppermint oil, relaxation therapy, cognitive behavioural therapy, and stress management have demonstrated efficacy in clinical trials for irritable bowel syndrome."],"references":["Ford AC, Sperber AD, Corsetti M, Camilleri M. Irritable bowel syndrome. Lancet. 2020 Nov 21;396(10263):1675-1688. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31548-8. Epub 2020 Oct 10. PMID: 33049223","Camilleri M. Diagnosis and Treatment of Irritable Bowel Syndrome: A Review. JAMA. 2021 Mar 2;325(9):865-877. doi: 10.1001/jama.2020.22532. Erratum in: JAMA. 2021 Apr 20;325(15):1568. doi: 10.1001/jama.2021.4833. PMID: 33651094","Patel N, Shackelford KB. Irritable Bowel Syndrome. [Updated 2022 Oct 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534810/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Scienc"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49051"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15388"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49051","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49051"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-21T19:21:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-21T19:22:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8079"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63604"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHea